  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Christian Leaders against Corruption in Education in Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Involvement of school level management in examination malpractices reduced
Decreased student desire and interest in corrupt educational practices
Set in place workable policies to make corruption an unattractive venture within the educational sector.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">a. The project implementation approach will be more right-based and beneficiaries will be involved through the various defined roles. 
b. The leaderships of the PTAs and the SMCs of the selected schools will be engaged to support the effort. 
c. There will be several high level engagements with relevant key stakeholders including the Parliamentary select committee on Education, WAEC, Ministry of Education and Ghana Education Service among others. 
d. The approach is multifaceted and uses the right holders through community capacity conversations, interaction of various individuals and selected key stakeholders. It is also very interactive with the social media components.</narrative>
  </description>
